chest.name: Bench press
chest.instructions: During a bench press, you lower the weight down to chest level and then press upwards while extending your arms.

chest.name: Push-ups
chest.instructions: Start in a high plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart, body straight from head to heels, and core engaged; slowly bend your elbows to lower your chest until itâ€™s just above the ground, then push through your palms to return to the starting position, keeping your form consistent throughout.

chest.name: Dumbbell fly
chest.instructions: Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended above your chest and palms facing each other; keep a slight bend in your elbows as you slowly lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position, maintaining control and form throughout the movement.

back.name: Pull-ups
back.instructions: Grip the pull-up bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width, palms facing away; start from a dead hang with arms fully extended, then engage your back and core to pull your chest toward the bar until your chin is above it, before slowly lowering yourself back to the starting position with control, maintaining proper form throughout.

back.name: Seated row
back.instructions: Sit on the row machine with your feet securely on the footrests and knees slightly bent; grasp the handle with both hands, keep your back straight, and engage your core; pull the handle toward your torso by squeezing your shoulder blades together, keeping your elbows close to your body, then slowly extend your arms back to the starting position, maintaining control and proper posture throughout.

back.name: Single arm dumbell row
back.instructions: Place your left knee and hand on a bench for support, keeping your back flat and core engaged; hold a dumbbell in your right hand with your arm fully extended; pull the dumbbell toward your torso by driving your elbow back and squeezing your shoulder blade, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control; repeat on the other side.

shoulders.name: Lateral raises
shoulders.instructions: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, arms by your sides and palms facing inward; keep a slight bend in your elbows as you lift the dumbbells out to the sides until they reach shoulder height, forming a 'T' shape, then slowly lower them back down to the starting position with control, keeping your core engaged and avoiding momentum.

shoulders.name: Arnold press
shoulders.instructions: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing your chest and elbows bent; as you press the dumbbells overhead, rotate your wrists outward so your palms face forward at the top of the movement, then reverse the motion to return to the starting position, maintaining control and proper form throughout.

shoulders.name: Dumbbell front raise
shoulders.instructions: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended in front of your thighs and palms facing your body; keep a slight bend in your elbows as you lift the dumbbells straight up in front of you to shoulder height, then slowly lower them back down to the starting position with control, keeping your core engaged and avoiding momentum.

biceps.name: Hammer curl
biceps.instructions: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended by your sides and palms facing inward; keep your elbows close to your body as you curl the dumbbells upward toward your shoulders, maintaining the neutral grip throughout, then slowly lower them back to the starting position with control, avoiding swinging or using momentum.

biceps.name: Cable curl
biceps.instructions: Stand facing a cable machine with the handle attached to the low pulley; grasp the handle with both hands, palms facing upward, and step back slightly to create tension; keep your elbows close to your torso as you curl the handle toward your chest, squeezing your biceps at the top, then slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control, maintaining proper posture throughout.

biceps.name: Dumbbell curl
biceps.instructions: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended by your sides, and palms facing forward; keep your elbows close to your body as you curl the dumbbells upward toward your shoulders, squeezing your biceps at the top, then slowly lower them back to the starting position with control, avoiding momentum or swinging.

triceps.name: Skull crusher
triceps.instructions: Lie flat on a bench with a barbell or dumbbells held straight above your chest, arms fully extended and palms facing forward; keeping your elbows stationary, lower the weight toward your forehead by bending your elbows, then extend your arms back to the starting position, focusing on engaging your triceps and maintaining control throughout.

triceps.name: Triceps pushdown
triceps.instructions: Stand facing a cable machine with the rope or bar attachment set at the high pulley; grasp the handle with an overhand grip, elbows bent at 90 degrees by your sides; keeping your elbows stationary, push the handle downward by extending your arms fully, squeezing your triceps at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position with control, maintaining a stable posture and avoiding swinging.

triceps.name: Bench dip
triceps.instructions: Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips and your feet flat on the floor, knees bent; slide your hips off the bench and lower your body by bending your elbows to about 90 degrees, keeping your elbows pointing straight back; then, press through your palms to straighten your arms and raise your body back to the starting position, maintaining control and avoiding swinging.
